main event: A unidentified flying object was reported in Elkins Park, Pennsylvania on February 17, 1967.
interesting points: Witness stated the object appeared to be about 50-75 feet in diameter and traveling at high speed,The object was observed for approximately 2-3 minutes before disappearing,No sound was heard during the observation,No physical trace evidence was found at the site,The original negative of the photo associated with the report was needed for further scientific investigation.
sighted object: an oval-shaped object in the sky
witness description: a family of four including adults and teenagers
